title: Manual React.js installation guide
summary: Learn how to install Page UI landing page components manually in your React.js app. Install Tailwind CSS to get started.

body.raw:
Learn how to install Page UI manually in your React.js app with TypeScript.
Skip the setup and use{' '} Shipixen {' '} to get a codebase with all components set up. } />
## Install dependencies ```bash npm install -D tailwindcss@3 postcss autoprefixer @tailwindcss/forms @tailwindcss/typography tailwindcss-animate embla-carousel-react class-variance-authority clsx tailwind-merge lucide-react @radix-ui/react-accordion @radix-ui/react-tabs @radix-ui/react-label ```
## Setup Tailwind CSS ```bash npx tailwindcss init -p ```
Or see how to install Tailwind CSS for your framework in the [Tailwind CSS documentation](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/installation/framework-guides).
## Add Page UI components and configuration - [tailwind.config.js](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/tailwind.config.ts) - [data/config/colors.js](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/data/config/colors.js) - [lib/utils.ts](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/lib/utils.ts) - [components/shared/ui/accordion.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/accordion.tsx) - [components/shared/ui/button.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/button.tsx) - [components/shared/ui/carousel.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/carousel.tsx) - [components/shared/ui/glow-bg.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/glow-bg.tsx) - [components/shared/Image.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/react/shared/Image.tsx) or if using Next.js, [get this](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/Image.tsx) - [components/shared/ui/input.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/input.tsx) - [components/shared/ui/label.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/ui/label.tsx) - [components/shared/VideoPlayer.tsx](https://github.com/danmindru/page-ui/blob/main/components/shared/VideoPlayer.tsx) - [ðŸ“š components/landing](https://cache.shipixen.com/page-ui%2Fcomponents.zip) (remember to unzip). The directory structure should look like this: ```bash data/ config/ colors.js src/ components/ shared/ ui/ accordion.tsx button.tsx glow-bg.tsx Image.tsx VideoPlayer.tsx landing/ ...unzip here lib/ utils.ts tailwind.config.js ```
## Configure TypeScript aliases Add the following code to the tsconfig.json file to resolve paths:
```diff-json:tsconfig.json { "compilerOptions": { + "baseUrl": ".", + "paths": { + "@/*": [ + "./src/*" + ] + }, // ...rest of your config } } ```
## Configure aliases for Vite or Webpack If you are using Vite, add the following code to the `vite.config.ts` so your app can resolve paths without error:
```bash npm i -D @types/node ``` ```diff-ts:vite.config.ts +import path from "path" import { defineConfig } from 'vite' import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react' // https://vitejs.dev/config/ export default defineConfig({ plugins: [react()], + resolve: { + alias: { + "@": path.resolve(__dirname, "./src"), + }, + }, }) ```
If you are using Webpack, you can add the following code to your `webpack.config.js` file: ```diff-js:webpack.config.js +const path = require('path'); module.exports = { + resolve: { + alias: { + '@': path.resolve(__dirname, 'src/'), + }, + }, // ...rest of your config }; ```
## Configure CSS Add the below to your main CSS file, usually `index.css`, `app.css`, or `global.css`.

## Troubleshooting Something not quite right? Check out the [sample repository](https://github.com/Shipixen/page-ui-react-vite-example) for a full working example. ## Theming Get new themes directly from the docs (open any component documentation â†’ select a theme from the dropdown and scroll down to copy to clipboard). You can also [explore themes here](https://shipixen.com/color-theme-explorer-shadcn). Alternatively, you can change `data/config/color.js` manually. ## Next steps Start adding components to your Next.js app.
- copy & paste any section from [templates](https://shipixen.com/demo/landing-page-templates) (turn on thief mode) - see a gigantic collection of [usage examples](https://shipixen.com/demo/landing-page-component-examples) - go to the [component documentation](/docs/landing-page-components) to find more usage examples and documentation on props and customization.
